    rationale: "Laminar flow consists of parallel fluid layers moving in an orderly fashion with no mixing between layers. It is governed by Poiseuille's Law (Q = \u03c0r\u2074\u0394P/8\u03b7L), is mathematically predictable, and is energy-efficient because kinetic energy is not wasted on eddy formation. Turbulent flow is chaotic, forms eddies and vortices, dissipates energy as heat and sound, and requires a greater pressure gradient to maintain the same flow rate. Turbulent flow is not more energy-efficient \u2014 eddies dissipate energy rather than recirculate it usefully. Laminar flow is highly predictable and stable under low Reynolds number conditions. The difference between laminar and turbulent flow is fundamental to physiology and clinical anesthesia, not merely visual.",
